<% content_for :title, "Privacy" %>

<div class="row justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-lg-8">
    <div class="card p-4 p-md-5">
      <h1 class="h2 mb-3">Privacy notice</h1>
      <p>Study Compass stores the information needed to operate the app: your name, email address, password digest, optional Canvas iCal URL, assignments you create or import, and study group activity (groups, memberships, and messages).</p>

      <h2 class="h5 mt-3">How we use your data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Authentication & account management (name, email, password digest).</li>
        <li>Syncing assignments via Canvas iCal when you provide an iCal URL.</li>
        <li>Displaying and persisting assignments, study groups, and messages you create.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="h5 mt-3">Data sharing and retention</h2>
      <p>We do not sell your personal data. Data is retained to provide the service and to allow account recovery. If you delete your account, we will remove personal data associated with that account from the application database.</p>

      <h2 class="h5 mt-3">Requesting deletion or export</h2>
      <p>To request deletion, sign in and remove your account from the app. If you need assistance, open an issue or contact the project maintainers using the repository linked in the site footer. You may also request an export of your assignments and groups via the same contact route.</p>

      <h2 class="h5 mt-3">AI features</h2>
      <p>The app may use an AI helper to generate study-plan suggestions. When AI is used, only summary data about your pending assignments is sent to the configured AI service. If an API key is not configured or the service is unavailable, the app falls back to a local summary generated on-device.</p>

      <p class="mt-3 mb-0">If you have questions, reach out via the repository linked in the footer.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
